{
  "title": "148863628.what Are You Competing On",
  "slug": "148863628what-are-you-competing-on",
  "publishedAt": "2025-11-30T19:30:04.307Z",
  "excerpt": "It’s all too easy to make a thing and expect people to simply show up.",
  "image": "",
  "readTime": "1 min",
  "content": [
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "It’s all too easy to make a thing and expect people to simply show up.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "We forget: the people we’re selling to,",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "they have options",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": ". Choosing one option means they’re",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "not",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "choosing another.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Which means that whether we’re making or selling a product, a person, a worldview, or a story, we’re always competing, all the time, for something.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Hence the value of the question: “What are you competing",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "on",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "?” (",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Not",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "“what are you competing",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "for",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "?”)",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Because while the latter is a relatively objective metric—specific to the problem at hand—the former, however, is not. There’s more than one way to build trust, gain attention, or inspire action, after all.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Being clear about what you’re competing on is how you zero-in on the metrics that really matter for the goal you’re trying to achieve.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Addressing and optimizing those metrics is how you create a thing that competes in a competitive marketplace, and that truly counts (toward making a difference for the people you're selling to).",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}